                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1810" notAfter="1936"><p>
                        While it lacks a ticket, the style closely comports with other by the <settlement>London</settlement> bookbinding firm of <persName type="standard" cert="high" role="bnd" key="">Charles Lewis</persName>. 
                        Sewn on four sawn-in <material>cords</material>, then laced into the <material>pasteboards</material>.
                        Decorative front-bead endbands at head and tail worked in <material>yellow silk</material> thread. 
                        Bound in full crimson straight-grained morocco goatskin <material>leather</material> with four false bands over a hollow tube on the spine.</p> 
                        <decoNote type="binding"><p>Elegantly tooled in both blind and <material>gold leaf</material> with an interlaced diaper and sqaure on the boards interspersed with as well as the spine, which is title <q xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">BAHARISTAN</q>.</p></decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                           <height>245</height>
                           <width>176</width>
                           <depth>36</depth>
                        </dimensions></p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
